version: 1
display_name: VCFA-9X-000375 - VMware Cloud Foundation Automation must disable unused feature flags.
global_description: |-
  VCF Automation can ship with alpha features that are still under development but in a state where some customers may find them useful. If not used these features should be disabled to reduce attack surface and risk that may be present in features not considered production ready.
osfinger:
  - VMware Photon OS-5
refs:
  disa_stig:
    - VCFA-9X-000375
  srg:
    - SRG-APP-000516
  cci:
    - CCI-000366
  nist:
    - CM-6 b
benchmark_id:
  vcf9_automation:
    type: custom
    desc: VMware Cloud Foundation Automation must disable unused feature flags.
    control_id: VCFA-9X-000375
    scored: true
    profile:
      - default
    information: |-
      If VCF Automation is not deployed, this is not applicable.

      From the VCF Automation Tenant Manager, go to Administration >> Feature Flags.

      Review the enabled feature flags and determine if any feature flags are enabled that are not actively used in the environment.

      If any feature flags are enabled and not actively used, this is a finding.
    rationale: |-
      VCF Automation can ship with alpha features that are still under development but in a state where some customers may find them useful. If not used these features should be disabled to reduce attack surface and risk that may be present in features not considered production ready.
    remediation: |-
      From the VCF Automation Tenant Manager, go to Administration >> Feature Flags.

      Click the menu button next to the target feature flag and select "Disable".
